body:
When using label wrapping, for some texts, the wrapping isn't performed correctly.

![label-wrap-bug](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/56004737/87057120-d8a6d700-c1dc-11ea-8a06-1250b8cbdc3f.png)

As you can see in the screenshot above, "water." text fits the line. In fact, if you add a blank space to the end (or an extra dot), it draws in a single line.

Code to reproduce:

```
public class LabelWrappingBug extends ApplicationAdapter {

	private BitmapFont bitmapFont;
	private Stage stage;
	
	@Override
	public void create () {
		stage = new Stage(new ScreenViewport());
		bitmapFont = new BitmapFont(Gdx.files.internal("ringbearer.fnt"));

		LabelStyle style = new LabelStyle(bitmapFont, Color.WHITE);
		Label label = new Label("It is filled with water.", style);
		label.setWrap(true);
		label.setAlignment(Align.center);

		Table table = new Table();
		table.add(label).prefWidth(600);

		table.setFillParent(true);

		table.debug();

		stage.addActor(table);
	}

	@Override
	public void render () {
		Gdx.gl.glClearColor(0, 0, 0, 1);
		Gdx.gl.glClear(GL20.GL_COLOR_BUFFER_BIT);

		stage.act();
		stage.draw();
	}
	
	@Override
	public void dispose () {
		stage.dispose();
		bitmapFont.dispose();
	}
}
```

Font files:

[ringbearer.zip](https://github.com/libgdx/libgdx/files/4897710/ringbearer.zip)

The LibGDX version I'm using is 1.9.10. I'm testing on Desktop, using Ubuntu 18.04 LTS. Java version is 1.8.0_201.

I believe the issue is explained here: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/43618643/libgdx-label-text-wrap-bug

It has something to do with second call to `layout.setText` in `Label` class, probably a rounding issue.

I suspect this is also causing the labels padding to be calculated wrong sometimes. For example (text is cut of on the right):

![bug-1](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/56004737/87058190-2a039600-c1de-11ea-9656-4aa3f40b2733.png)
![bug-2](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/56004737/87058203-2d971d00-c1de-11ea-88bf-15d73cb2c6fd.png)

Let me know if you need more information and if I can help somehow! Kind regards, Lucas.
